  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age at diagnosis ≥ 18 to ≤ 55 years

          -  Employed at the entry into the care pathway

          -  Presenting an upper aero-digestive tract cancer (excluding nasal cavities), stage I,
             II and III, under a first anti-tumor treatment (surgery, radiotherapy, or
             chemotherapy)

          -  Patient mastering the French language

          -  Affiliated to the social security system

          -  Consent signed by the patient before the implementation of any specific study
             procedure

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Having been treated for another cancer before (except skin cancer and / or prostate)

          -  Metastatic disease from the outset

          -  Patient unable to submit to a regular follow-up

          -  Presenting psychiatric disorders
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
